Certainly! You can achieve this by customizing the column menu in sap.ui.table with a custom menu item for clearing the filter. Here's an example code snippet to demonstrate how you can do this:

```javascript
// Define your table and columns
var oTable = new sap.ui.table.Table({
  // your table properties here
});

var oColumn = new sap.ui.table.Column({
  label: "Column 1",
  template: "column1",
  filterProperty: "column1",
  sortProperty: "column1",
});

// Add custom menu item for clearing filter
var oColumnMenu = oColumn.getMenu();
oColumnMenu.addItem(new sap.ui.unified.MenuItem({
  text: "Clear Filter",
  select: function() {
    oTable.filter(oColumn, ''); // Clear the filter for the current column
  }
}));

oTable.addColumn(oColumn);
oTable.bindRows("/yourModel");

// Finally, add the table to the page
oTable.placeAt("content");
```

In this code snippet, we first define a table with a column. We then customize the column menu by adding a custom menu item "Clear Filter" for resetting the filter of the current column. When the user clicks this menu item, the `select` event handler is triggered which clears the filter for the current column.

